org.dockbox.selene.proxy.annotations

Annotation Type Proxy.Target


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value=METHOD)
public static @interface Proxy.Target
    The annotation used to mark a method as proxy executor. When method() is unchanged, the name of the annotated method will be used when looking up the target method in the target type. Any parameters not annotated with Instance will be used during lookup, in the exact order they are defined.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      Phase at
      At which Phase the proxy executor should be performed.
      java.lang.String method
      The name of the method to target, without parameter or class qualifiers.
      boolean overwrite
      Whether or not to overwrite the return value of the target method.
      int priority
      The priority of the proxy executor.
